<concept id="concept_49720D8D6FB14642961861F47C12A89D">
  <title>Open Source Media Framework (OSMF)</title>
  <shortdesc>For most OSMF players we recommend using the AppMeasurement
	 plug-in for OSMF. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <keyword>media</keyword>
        <keyword>milestone</keyword>
        <keyword>sdk</keyword>
        <keyword>video</keyword>
      </keywords>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Developer and implementation" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody>
    <p> This plug-in provides an instance of AppMeasurement auto-track support
		for OSMF players, and adds a reference plug-in to OSMF players that captures
		media data and events. 
	 </p>
    <p>First, 
		<xref href="video_osmf_download.xml#task_C318D1EDA2824C1BA2C1A325F359F85F" type="task" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Download the Media Module for OSMF?></xref>.
		You can add video measurement for OSMF using one of the following methods: 
	 </p>
    <table id="table_2F574F59F15146C096C3BF51F826643C">
      <tgroup cols="3">
        <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="1.00*" />
        <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="1.70*" />
        <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3" colwidth="1.35*" />
        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry colname="col1">Implementation Method 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col2">Description 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col3">Guide 
				</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry colname="col1">Dynamic Plug-in 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col2">The dynamic implementation links the plug-in
				  into your Flash project at run-time. A dynamic implementation lets you manage
				  the OSMF player separately from AppMeasurement tracking code using an XML
				  configuration file. 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col3">
              <xref href="video_osmf_dynamic.xml#concept_20417E8BA5FE45D0A2DA8A271669E559" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local">
                <?xm-replace_text Dynamic Implementation?>
              </xref>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry colname="col1">Custom Dynamic Plug-in 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col2">This lets you extend the dynamic plug-in if
				  you need to send additional metrics using Media.Monitor. 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col3">
              <xref href="video_osmf_dynamic_custom.xml#concept_B00E2B15A2EF4F46A89FA887929FFCFD" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local">
                <?xm-replace_text Custom Dynamic Implementation?>
              </xref>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry colname="col1">Static 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col2">The static implementation links
				  AppMeasurement_Media_AutoTrackOSMF.swc into your Flash project. You can then
				  configure video measurement using the library directly. 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col3">
              <xref href="video_osmf_static.xml#concept_982C32CC35CE44F8A3543DF9AD741C83" format="dita" scope="local">
                <?xm-replace_text Static Implementation?>
              </xref>
            </entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
  </conbody>
</concept>